Glencore to Build Oil-Seed Crusher in Ukraine, Kommersant Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-03-02T08:21:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/glencore-to-build-oil-seed-crusher-in-ukraine-kommersant-says.html
Glencore International AG will
invest 523 million hryvnia ($66 million) to build an oil-seed
crushing plant in  Ukraine â€™s Odessa region,  Kommersant-Ukraine 
reported, citing a regional administration official.  The investment will be made in two stages, with 250 million
hryvnia spent this year and 273 million next year, the Kiev-
based newspaper said, citing Economy Department head Oleg
Muratov. The plant will have an annual processing capacity of
2,500 metric tons of sunflower seeds, 2,000 tons of rapeseeds
and 1,600 tons of soya, according to Kommersant.  To contact the reporter on this story:
